description.plain:
Claudia Feliciano (born June 24, 1987), better known by her stage name Snow Tha Product, is a Mexican-American rapper and singer, signed to Atlantic Records.

Snow is mostly known for her singles “Holy Shi!” and “Drunk Love” and her mixtape Good Nights & Bad Mornings.

She released her first independent album Unorthodox in 2011 to positive reviews.
Her first EP on Atlantic was released in June 2016 and titled, Half Way There, Pt. 1.

This track was released on August 7th, 2014. Three days earlier, Nicki Minaj released Anaconda, with the single’s artwork depicting Minaj squatting, only sporting a thong.

Snow is frustrated with the way women are depicted in hip-hop as being an ass on a pair of legs. However, she calls out the women at fault, Minaj and Australian emcee Iggy Azalea.

Officially unreleased, the song was posted on Snow’s SoundCloud account on October 27, 2016.

In “Bilingüe”, Snow Tha Product celebrates her multicultural identity. Having grown up in the United States and Mexico, Snow channels influences from both countries and fuses them together.

The song was released on March 19, 2019 along with a music video.

For the iTunes Latino Charts for the Songs category, “Bilingüe” has reached #6 and it’s also reached #32 on the Hip-Hop Charts.

songs.title: Say Bitch

description.plain:
On this track, Snow Tha Product questions why women always seem to hate on other women instead of supporting and uplifting each other while also adding a little boss talk about how hard she has been grinding for many years and how it’s finally paying off in multiple ways. Snow also touches on how people could use their time more wisely instead of hating on social media and that females should choose better partners instead of the type of men that would likely be considered “L’s”.

On the first day of release, the song reached #9 on Hip-Hop/Rap Genre and #73 on All Genres on US iTunes charts.

The music video for the song features Snow and a bunch of women having fun and turning up together, highlighting the fact that there doesn’t have to be a competition between females. At the end is a snippet for her upcoming single, “Not Today” which features Juicy J. The music video made it to #11 trending on YouTube the same day it dropped. The video also reached 1 million views within 4 days of its release, making it her fastest video to date to do so.

After doing so well on both iTunes and Youtube on release day, Snow posted on her social medias that she was grateful and that if fans continued to support her efforts, she would keep going hard.
